    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>If you need to know how many times a file is downloaded by your visitors then this plugin is for you! Just insert a simple shortcode and that&#8217;s it! You can also a simple parameter to any download link and the count will be done too!</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://remicorson.com\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Developer Website</a> &#8211; <a href=\"http://remicorson.com/easy-download-media-counter-free/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Dedicated Plugin Page</a></p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the entire &#8216;easy-download-media-counter&#8217; folder to the &#8216;/wp-content/plugins/&#8217; directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n<li>Upload a media to the WordPress library or pick an existing file</li>\n<li>Add to any url this: ?edmc=xxx (replace &#8220;xxx&#8221; by the media ID), ex: http://mysite.com/?edmc=123, or use this shortcode [edmc id=&#8221;xxx&#8221;] (this is an auto created link)</li>\n<li>Insert this shortcode in any page/post/CPT: [edmc_show id=&#8221;xxx&#8221;] (replace &#8220;xxx&#8221; by the media ID) to display the counter</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added downloads columns to library.</li>\n</ul>\n"
